                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/5287: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-05T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 5, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Reference is made to your telegram No. 50 of November 5, 4 p.m. Inform the
                    Greek Government and the International Finance Commission immediately that the
                    Government of the United States, in the absence of a satisfactory acceptance by
                    Greece of the President’s proposal regarding the suspension of intergovernmental
                    debts, has not authorized and cannot authorize the International Finance
                    Commission to suspend payment.</p>
                <p>We have had extensive discussions with the Greek Minister in the matter; he fully
                    understands our position and informs us that he has communicated it to his
                    Government. We have told the Minister that as soon as the President’s proposal
                    is accepted by the Greek Government, we will make every effort to secure at once
                    the consent of the Treasury Department to a suspension of the Greek payments to
                    this Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
